                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Winship Mission/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Commissioner for Liberia (<persName type="from"
                            >Winship</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-12T16:00:00-00:44"
                            >April 12, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Your telegram No. 23, April 11, 6 p.m. Saw Barclay this afternoon and
                    arranged for him to receive Lyle tomorrow for commencement of negotiations, with
                    full assurance that nothing would arise in the meantime to aggravate the present
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winship</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
